12959 of the total 12999 were represented in the blastp results. It means that only a small portion of the generated peptide tiles are not aligned to the NCBI Reference Sequences (RefSeq) for the 7 human coronaviruses.

Filtering the top hits only

Here, we defined top hits as:

  1. sseqid with the highest bitscore
  2. sseqid with the highest pident (percent identity)
  3. And the alignment must be at least 28 aa long
#Filtering the top hits only (highest bitscore, top pident, only those with 28aa or more aligned are selected)
blastp_top <- blastp %>%
  ungroup %>%
  group_by(qseqid) %>%
  slice_max(order_by = bitscore, with_ties = T, n = 1) %>%
  slice_max(order_by = pident, with_ties = T, n = 1)%>%
  filter(length >= 28)

blastp_top_single <- c(blastp_top %>%
  ungroup %>%
  count(qseqid) %>%
  filter(n == 1))$qseqid

blastp_top_mult <- c(blastp_top %>%
                       ungroup %>%
                       count(qseqid) %>%
                       filter(n != 1))$qseqid

Filtering algorithm - for those with multiple top hits

#Here we choose better scores, i.e. higher pident 
blastp_top_mult_resolve <- blastp_top %>%
  ungroup %>%
  select(-stitle) %>%
  filter(qseqid %in% blastp_top_mult) %>% distinct

# View(blastp_top_mult_resolve %>% count(qseqid, sort = T) %>% filter(n>1) %>% left_join(y = blastp_top_mult_resolve))

#Items with more than one annotation will be annotated according to original intention
dupl_acc <- c(blastp_top_mult_resolve %>% ungroup %>% select(qseqid) %>% distinct() %>%
  mutate(accession = str_extract(qseqid, regex("^[A-Za-z0-9_]+"))) %>%
  select(accession) %>% distinct)$accession

dupl_acc_ident <- tibble(accession = as.character(), staxid = as.character(), organism_label = as.character(), product = as.character())

#Looping to identify the original annotation
for (k in dupl_acc){
  print(k)
  entrez_summary_temp <- entrez_summary(db = "protein", id = entrez_search(db = "protein", term = k)$ids)
  dupl_acc_ident_temp <- tibble(accession = k, 
                                staxid = as.character(entrez_summary_temp$taxid), 
                                organism_label = entrez_summary_temp$organism, 
                                product = entrez_summary_temp$title)
  dupl_acc_ident <- bind_rows(dupl_acc_ident,dupl_acc_ident_temp)
  
}

Harmonizing the label of the downloaded entrez data

#Harmonizing the label
dupl_acc_ident_harmomnized <- dupl_acc_ident %>%
  mutate(label_harmonized = case_when(organism_label == "SARS coronavirus P2" ~ "sars",
                                      organism_label == "Human coronavirus NL63" ~ "nl63",
                                      organism_label == "Human coronavirus 229E" ~ "229e",
                                      organism_label == "Human coronavirus HKU1" ~ "hku1",
                                      organism_label == "Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2" ~ "sars2"),
         product_harmonized = case_when(str_detect(product, "spike") ~ "S",
                                        str_detect(product, "membrane") ~ "M",
                                        str_detect(product, "protein S") ~ "S",
                                        str_detect(product, "envelope") ~ "E",
                                        str_detect(product, "surface") ~ "S",
                                        str_detect(product, "nucleocapsid") ~ "N",
                                        str_detect(product, "orf7b") ~ "ORF7b"))


blastp_top_mult_resolve_extract <- blastp_top_mult_resolve %>%
  ungroup %>%
  select(qseqid, sseqid, sstart, send) %>%
  mutate(organism = str_extract(sseqid, regex("^[A-Za-z0-9]+")), accession = str_extract(qseqid, regex("^[A-Za-z0-9_]+"))) %>%
  left_join(y = dupl_acc_ident_harmomnized, by = c("accession", "organism" = "label_harmonized")) %>%
  filter(!is.na(staxid)) %>%
  mutate(stitle = paste0(organism, "-", product_harmonized)) %>%
  select(qseqid, stitle, sstart, send)

Combining the two unique and non-unique top-hit groups to yeild the full annotation

#Annotating and combining with the original annotation
combined_annot <- blastp_top %>%
  ungroup %>%
  filter(qseqid %in% blastp_top_single) %>%
  select(qseqid, stitle, sstart, send) %>%
  bind_rows(blastp_top_mult_resolve_extract) %>%
  mutate(specie_label = str_extract(stitle, regex("^[A-Za-z0-9]+")), 
         product_label = str_extract(str_extract(stitle, regex("-[A-Za-z0-9]+")), regex("[A-Za-z0-9]+"))) %>%
  ungroup()

Quality Control

datatable(combined_annot %>% count(specie_label, product_label))
datatable(combined_annot %>% count(specie_label))
#Plotting the peptide tile representation of S, E, M and N, needed for the for loop
virus_list <- c(combined_annot %>% select(specie_label) %>% distinct())$specie_label

#For Loop to create the plots
for (j in virus_list){
  print(j)
  p1.temp <- ggplot(combined_annot %>% 
                      filter(product_label %in% c("S", "E", "M", "N"),specie_label == j) %>%
                      mutate(product_label = fct_relevel(product_label,c("S","E","M","N")),
                             qseqid = fct_reorder(qseqid, (sstart))), 
                    aes(x = sstart, xend = send, y = qseqid, yend = qseqid))+
    geom_segment()+
    facet_grid(product_label~., scales = "free")+
    theme_bw()+
    theme(axis.text.y = element_blank())+
    labs(x = "AA Position Number", y = "Peptide Tile", title = paste0("Peptide tiles annotated to the Human Coronavirus ", j))
  
  print(p1.temp)
  
#ggsave(p1.temp, filename = paste0("qc_output/p1_peptidetile_alignedto_",j,".png"), height = 6, width = 16)
    
}
